    "body": "### Contact Details (e.g. Tox ID or email)\n\n_No response_\n\n### qTox Version\n\n1.18.2\n\n### Commit Hash\n\n_No response_\n\n### Toxcore Version\n\n_No response_\n\n### Qt Version\n\n_No response_\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Start qTox (maybe run the qTox on a dual monitor system)\n2. Start a video call\n3. Press the \"full screen\" button\n4. Press the \"Esc\" button\n\n### Observed Behavior\n\nThe video call does not expand to the full screen, only to about half the screen. The \"Esc\" button does not return the video call to the conversation window.\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\nThe video should expand to full screen. If one of the monitors is selected as the video source, the video call should expand to the other monitor. When you click the \"Esc\" button, the video call should return to the conversation window. These actions can be repeated several times. If during a call I switch the video source to another monitor, and the video call is expanded to full screen on this monitor, the video call should move to a monitor different from the source.\n\n### Reproducibility\n\nAlways\n\n### Operating System\n\nWindows\n\n### Operating System version/distro/name/etc.\n\n11\n\n### Relevant log output\n\n```shell\n\n```",
